From dd244257ed676fa8ffc3ed8708f9ccc2a4e60a7a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Steele <david@pgmasters.net>
Date: Tue, 26 Nov 2024 11:03:27 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 8/9] Use lz4 for protocol compression.

lz4 provides much better compression speed and gives similar compression ratios to gz when used at low levels (the gz default was 3).
---
 doc/xml/release/2025/2.55.0.xml    | 11 +++++++++++
 src/build/config/config.yaml       |  4 ++--
 src/config/parse.auto.c.inc        | 26 +++++++++++++-------------
 src/storage/remote/read.c          |  4 ++--
 src/storage/remote/write.c         |  7 +++++--
 test/src/module/command/helpTest.c |  2 +-
 test/src/module/config/parseTest.c | 20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 7 files changed, 54 insertions(+), 20 deletions(-)

diff --git a/doc/xml/release/2025/2.55.0.xml b/doc/xml/release/2025/2.55.0.xml
